This paper proposes a new architecture for improving feature pyramid networks commonly used in instance segmentation networks. The paper focuses on improving the accuracy of object detection and segmentation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The proposed architecture involves learning new correlations from feature maps, which is a common technique in deep learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses enhancing the semantic information of the feature pyramid, which is related to natural language processing (cs.CL).
